1.name: Shifted Star
1.desc:
A special crystalline matter observed by the Mimir system and which is high in value.
—A crystalized glow that is a coalescence of cause and effect which ceased to exist due to the deviation of the Idealbild. Contains one of the world's possible futures.

2.name: Ain Soph Coin
2.desc:
The digital currency issued by the CORG. Valid for transactions in the Sephirah Zone and is also the currency of Ain Soph.
—True value will make all truths hold their tongues.

3.name: Friendship Points
3.desc: Points obtained through interactions with friends.

4.name: Swigs
4.desc:
Swigs denote the remaining functional value of Mimir.
—Named after the sound Mimir makes when drinking Coolant. Timely replenishment of Swigs will ensure the system functions normally.

5.name: Modifier Scan Voucher
5.desc:
A data card that allows access to Mimir's vibrant resonation. Used to detect Modifiers by Scanning for them in a target area. Made by Aether Gazer, and given to the Administrator.
—As resonation imprints require a large amount of computational power from the Mimir system, activation authority has to be strictly controlled.

6.name: Name Change Card
6.desc:
Use to change the Admin's Username in the Mimir System.
—Forever hold the courage to seek the next star.

7.name: Guild Badge
7.desc: Awarded to guild members in recognition of their contribution to the guild. Use to redeem various items at the Guild Shop.

8.name: Guild Popularity
8.desc: Points obtained through activities in your guild.

10.name: Auguraze
10.desc: The world's most ubiquitous and valuable hard currency. It's said that the light it emits will cause those who look at it to gradually lose their ability to reason.

11.name: Chromeow Coin
11.desc: A special currency that isn't commonly used outside. Based on its name, it seems the raw material used in its production is related to Chromastal.

12.name: Admin EXP
12.desc:

—Believe in yourself and work hard to become a qualified Administrator.

14.name: Contract EXP
14.desc:

—As stated by the contract, we shall provide you with as much support as deemed necessary.

5000.desc:

—Pawww... are you really not buying something, meow?

6000.desc: The working space of Aether Gazer's General Office, equipped with a highly efficient standard processing system.

6001.name: Twilight Pearl
6001.desc:
High-level access credentials allowing for free, unlimited use of specified locations.
A premium business yacht that set Valleyrand Group back a pretty penny, the Twilight Pearl was later transferred to Aether Gazer and is often used for business negotiations.
6001.desc_source: Obtain by participating in Banquet Invitation event

6002.desc:

6002.desc_source: Obtain by participating in Banquet Invitation event

6003.name: VIP Care
6003.desc:
After the first aid lecture ends, Kuninotokotachi has you remain in the ward.
"Looks like you could use a little one-on-one nursing demonstration. Shall I show you how it's done?"

6004.name: Red Pavilion Whispers
6004.desc:
After returning from a visit to an old tomb, Lingguang hopes you can stay a little while longer.
—"You know... I'm only wearing this outfit for you. After tonight, it's going back in the closet... and it's staying there."

6005.name: See You Again
6005.desc:
After a fun day out, Zhiming seems somewhat reluctant to take you to the water's edge and fulfill the promise he just lost on the bet.
"Stay close to me... but not that close! Yes, that should be fine... Okay..."

6006.name: Untouchable
6006.desc:
It's the trill of the phoenix flute, the shadows of the lanterns, your laughter as it rings out above the hustle and bustle of the city.
"I'm just tired—it feels like you've been dragging me around all day. What is it you're expecting, exactly?"

6007.name: Courtyard Echoes
6007.desc: The afternoon sun, tipsy wind, and intoxicating fragrance of flowers. This piece is an unforgettable and poignant commemoration of us.

6008.name: Have A Dance With Me?
6008.desc: This dance is just for you, Admin. The figure is graceful and smells faintly of orchids. It's hard to ascertain whether this is a moment of serenity, or just all a dream.

6009.name: Time to Relax
6009.desc: The chance encounter in the elevator has shown people a different side to Gengchen. Maybe tailor-made clothes are never as good as we want them to be?

6010.name: Moment of Panic
6010.desc: I'm always very organized with work, but for some reason I always make mistakes whenever you're nearby. I didn't know you panicked like that too.

6011.name: Sleepwalker
6011.desc: As night falls, Admin comes across a girl immersed in a sweet dream. In the silent twilight, the only thing that moves is time.

6012.name: That First Glimmer of Light
6012.desc: Never-seen-before landscapes, unfamiliar shores... It's all a bit overwhelming for a young lady. What's Admin up to this time?

6013.name: Gentle Echo
6013.desc:
It's a scene Poseidon has always loved, and you're the only one she wants to share it with.
Let's turn that summer into the best of memories.
6013.desc_source: Obtain by participating in the Echoes of the Ocean event

6014.name: Amid Moonlight
6014.desc: As the evening breeze wafted through Selene's hair, this small world felt calm and quiet yet bursting with meaning. The waves were as gentle as the moonlit sky, while the moon seemed to be gazing back at her.

6015.name: Maiden's Daydream
6015.desc: The young lady had purchased a drink to pass the time waiting for the Admin to get back, but for some reason, whenever she was with the Admin, the pace of her steps always seemed to get disrupted...

6016.name: Afternoon Delight
6016.desc: That afternoon in the room, were Brahmā's sudden words true or false? Unfortunately, she's the only one who knows the answer.

6100.name: Command Center Lobby
6100.desc: The Aether Gazer Command Center Lobby is where Division Nine conducts its combat intel analysis and calculations, and it's here that the Admin often carries out preliminary operational planning.

"No... I just want to know if placing them like that was intentional or accidental."

10002.desc: "Thank goodness I'm a human and haven't lost my desire to find out more about the world. This is how I know I'm still me."
10002.desc_source: Obtain after completing the Elderly Writer Goes on An Adventure achievement.

10003.name: SGS Entry Ticket
10003.desc: "There must be plenty of other girls in the spotlight who, like me, have the power to bring smiles to other people's faces because of you."
10003.desc_source: Obtain after completing the Shine On, Idol Girl! achievement.

10004.name: N.E.Fingers Ⅲ
10004.desc: "I'm not crazy, I'm fine. I need to keep working so I can get back to my old life." "Hard work, progress, stay humble... That's a happy life..."
10004.desc_source: Obtain after completing the Cyber Ailment: 2315 achievement.

—An Access Key upgrade module developed by the Cryptics that enhances a Modifier's control of Divine Power through their Access Key. It is now in the stability testing phase.

40309.name: Chip Expansion - Thunder
40309.desc:
Used to increase a Modifier's attributes.
—An Access Key upgrade module developed by the Cryptics that enhances a Modifier's control of Divine Power through their Access Key. It is now in the stability testing phase.

40310.name: Chip Expansion
40310.desc:
Symbolizes a Chip Expansion with any attributes.
——It's for display purposes only, and doesn't really have any use.

40411.name: Origin Dust
40411.desc:
Special item used for Modifier LimitBreak.
—The powers of the Modifiers have been lost in the Source Layer due to numerous era changes. These lost powers have slowly substantialized at the bottom of the Source Layer.

40412.name: Origin Star Whirl
40412.desc:
Special item used for Modifier LimitBreak.
—Even lost dust follows the rhythm of the Gen-zone.

40413.name: Origin Condensation
40413.desc:
Special item used for Modifier LimitBreak.
—Fallen leaves return to the land, merging into whence they came.

40414.name: Origin Radiance
40414.desc:
Special item used for Modifier LimitBreak.
—A fragment of power that has long since settled beyond sense, reaching its final form by continuously absorbing more and more Divine Power.

40415.name: Origin Firmament
40415.desc:
A Modifier exclusive item that can be used to break through their own limitations.
—There are no boundaries or shapes, just a series of connections from a hazy memory.

40501.name: Spirit Extract T1
40501.desc:
An extract containing mysterious energy used for low-level LimitBreak of Access Keys and Sigils.
—Spring water from the depths of the Source Layer, obtained through further extraction.

40502.name: Spirit Extract T2
40502.desc:
An extract containing mysterious energy used for mid-level LimitBreak of Access Keys and Sigils.
—Spring water from the depths of the Source Layer, obtained through further extraction.

40503.name: Spirit Extract T3
40503.desc:
An extract containing mysterious energy used for high-level LimitBreak of Access Keys and Sigils.
—Spring water from the depths of the Source Layer, obtained through further extraction.

40504.name: Spirit Extract T4
40504.desc:
An extract containing mysterious energy used for ultimate-level LimitBreak of Access Keys and Sigils.
—Spring water from the depths of the Source Layer, obtained through further extraction.

40601.name: Sigil Module T1
40601.desc:
Generates 1 random Sigil skill.
—A special module that can attach skills to Sigils. It contains a small amount of Divine Power that will combine with the Sigil once they come into contact.

40602.name: Sigil Module T2
40602.desc:
Generates 1 random Sigil skill.
—A special module that can attach skills to Sigils. It contains a moderate amount of Divine Power that will combine with the Sigil once they come into contact.

40603.name: Sigil Module T3
40603.desc:
Generates 2 random Sigil skills.
—A special module that can attach skills to Sigils. It contains a large amount of Divine Power that will combine with the Sigil once they come into contact.

40604.name: Precise Sigil Module
40604.desc:
Select 1 skill to apply the Sigil.
—A finely crafted special module that channels Divine Power to fuse Sigils, attaching the Sigil to the selected ability.

40701.name: Reconstructor
40701.desc:
A special apparatus that is used in high-level Sigil reconstruction. It can randomly change the Gen-zone of the Sigil.
—A reflection of The Cryptics' technological prowess.

40801.name: Revelation T1
40801.desc:
Grants 50 Sigil EXP.
—A special material that's used to enhance Sigils and increase Sigil EXP by a small amount.

40802.name: Revelation T2
40802.desc:
Grants 100 Sigil EXP.
—A special material that's used to enhance Sigils and increase Sigil EXP by a moderate amount.

40803.name: Revelation T3
40803.desc:
Grants 500 Sigil EXP.
—A special material that's used to enhance Sigils and increase Sigil EXP by a great amount.

40901.name: Intel Crest (A)
40901.desc:
Can be exchanged for Intel on B-Grade and A-Grade Modifiers.
—Thank you for helping the organization gather intel!

40902.name: Intel Crest (S)
40902.desc:
Can be exchanged for intel on S-Grade Modifiers.
—Thank you for helping the organization gather intel!

41001.name: Sigil Shard
41001.desc:
A special shard obtained from breaking down 3 and 4-Star Sigils. Collect a certain amount to exchange them for 3 or 4-Star Sigils.
—A byproduct of experiments where Sigils are shattered in the process.

41002.name: Sigil Core
41002.desc:
A special shard obtained from breaking down 5-Star Sigils. Collect a certain amount to exchange them for 5-Star Sigils.
—Ashes to ashes, dust to dust.

41101.name: Hazard Zone Beacon
41101.desc:
An item that's used to maintain the stability of the Modifier's consciousness, and is able to provide guidance to the Mod in the Hazard Zone.
—A bearer of light in the darkness to illuminate the way ahead.

41201.name: Transcendence Crystal
41201.desc:
Used to help in high-level Functor enhancement and transcendence.
—A data crystal that has been condensed from the memories of the Functors scattered in Gaea's ocean of consciousness.

41301.name: Function Factor T1
41301.desc:
Use to increase a Sigil's Warp Effect level.
—Find the self that was lost in the endless Cycle.

41302.name: Function Factor T2
41302.desc:
Use to increase a Sigil's Warp Effect level.
—Find the self that was lost in the endless Cycle.

41303.name: Polymerized Function Crystal
41303.desc:
Use to increase a Sigil's Warp Effect level.
—Find the self that was lost in the endless Cycle.

41401.name: Star Anchor
41401.desc:
Use for high-level Sigil forging.
—It watches the birth and dissipation of all things, bearing witness to the continuous succession of wills.

41501.name: Calibration Component
41501.desc:
Use to unlock Synergy between the Mods and their Access Keys and increase the Synergy Rate.
—A tool kit used by the Cryptics to adjust Modifier's Access Keys. But be sure to make a preliminary check up before using it, otherwise it might result in the discovery of some special things placed in there by Ookuninushi.

<color=#9A9A9A>Obtain from limited events.</color>

41601.name: Operation Record
41601.desc:
Used to retrace a Modifier's past.
—All of these fractured past experiences combined comprise a complete "person".

41701.name: Dorm Fund
41701.desc: Use this item to unlock the dorms. Spend Park Stamps to obtain it!

50001.name: Brand New Notebook
50001.desc: A simple but very practical notebook. It might come in handy if given to someone with lots to do...

50002.name: BBQ Shop Coupon
50002.desc: A 20% discount coupon that's valid for a limited time at a popular BBQ shop. It says if two people dine together, the discount is increased to 30% off. It's a great deal for lovers of barbecue.

50003.name: Materials for Needlework
50003.desc: The textile industry has been fully automated, but there are still people who hand-knit gifts, stitch by stitch, for those important to them.

50004.name: Super Heavy Dumbbells
50004.desc: A pair of heavy dumbbells that looks perfect for bodybuilders.

50005.name: Investigations Handbook
50005.desc: A handbook for recording clues and confessions. Looks extremely useful to an investigator.

50006.name: Gaming Device
50006.desc: The latest GFV handheld gaming device. Gamers would love this thing.

50007.name: Conch Necklace
50007.desc: A necklace that's just a conch on a string. It doesn't look like much, but people who like nature and the sea would surely appreciate it...

50008.name: Metal Mane Comb
50008.desc: A tool for grooming your horse's mane to keep it neat and shining. Riders who spend time with their horses daily could really use this...

50009.name: Gentleman's Bow Tie
50009.desc: A delicate red bow tie. It would definitely complement a dignified gentleman who takes great pride in his appearance.

50010.name: Golf Club
50010.desc: An expensive, high-quality golf club. It's supposedly able to guarantee that every swing will hit the hole.

50011.name: Colorful Ice Stick
50011.desc: A rainbow ice stick with a unique taste. Children who love that crispy, chilly rush won't be able to resist this yummy treat.

50012.name: Rubber Frisbee
50012.desc: A fluorescent frisbee that glides in the air for a long long time. One of such frisbees plus YOU can keep your doggy happy for a day.

50013.name: Horse Ranch Postcard
50013.desc: A commemorative postcard issued in conjunction with a horse ranch, featuring famous equine prizewinners.

50014.name: Silver Star Coin
50014.desc: An old, odd-looking star coin found by chance in some ruins. It's believed to be an item used by ancients to perform tarot divination...

50015.name: Sake Pot
50015.desc: A rustic and delicate sake pot. Someone who loves imbibing spirits would be pleased to have it as a gift...

50016.name: Ancient Chess Record
50016.desc: An ancient record of chess games found by chance in some ruins. Some of the pages have been lost permanently. However, that might make it even more valuable to a serious chess player who loves to study the moves...

50017.name: Light Music CD
50017.desc: A CD containing light music that was recorded by a small chamber orchestra. Suitable for people who love sitting back and appreciating the acoustic art...

50018.name: Warrior's Omamori
50018.desc: A kendo figure is sewn on it. It feels like something a kendo practitioner would wear...

50019.name: Haute Perfume
50019.desc: An expensive brand-name perfume. One drop can keep the fragrance all day. Perhaps this will please a certain lady...

50020.name: Music Box
50020.desc: A music box with two dolls that move around the center like carousel horses when you wind it up.

50021.name: Soft Pillow
50021.desc: A large pillow that looks very comfy. Cuddling it will put you right to sleep...

50022.name: Broken Doll
50022.desc: A small bear doll that has a patch sewn over its right eye. It was abandoned because of its ominous aura. Maybe someone who had experienced similar loneliness can be friends with it...

50023.name: Cap
50023.desc: A practical and lightweight black cap, suitable for people who are often on the move and need some protection from the sun and wind.

50024.name: Omorfies Essential Oil
50024.desc: A bottle of essential oil produced in Omorfies that has rosemary as its main ingredient. Someone said that it's "a treasure that gives me charm and vitality"...

50025.name: Espresso Capsule
50025.desc: One espresso capsule can make 600 ml of strong coffee. It's an indispensable item for those who often need to stay up late to work...

50026.name: Fishing Master's Rod
50026.desc: Nicknamed the "Coastline Dominator," it's rumored that only fishing experts can handle this rod.

50027.name: Chisel Set for Beginners
50027.desc: These chiseling tools are not as complete as what an advanced set has, but they are more suitable for creators who have not reached the peak of their skills.

50028.name: Fingerless Boxing Gloves
50028.desc: Studded, with mysterious totems printed on them. These half gloves have a certain aura about them, and look like powerful equipment that martial arts enthusiasts would love...

50029.name: Curry Powder
50029.desc:
An indispensable ingredient for making authentic curries.
This should be popular with Modifiers who like curry and cooking...

50030.name: Boat Grill Set
50030.desc:
A portable grill set that can be brought onto a boat.
This should be a hit with Modifiers who love to go out to sea and enjoy grilling...

50031.name: Fine Puppet Pigment
50031.desc:
Mineral pigments used by professional puppet makers.
This will make a great gift for someone who likes making puppets...

50032.name: Cigar Cutter
50032.desc: Although most cigars on the market are made to be enjoyed immediately, there are still plenty of old-school cigar aficionados who prefer the type that needs to be clipped at one end with a cigar cutter first.

50033.name: Rostach Pocketknife
50033.desc: The preferred pocketknife of Rostach's bounty hunter guilds. This would make a perfect gift for a weapon collector.

50034.name: Tambourine
50034.desc: A tambourine adorned with brightly colored feathers. This would definitely make a great gift for someone who loves to dance...

50035.name: VR Gaming & Training Device
50035.desc: Developed by Aether Gazer, a state-of-the-art gaming device uploaded with high-quality Visbane simulation battle games. Given to someone who both works hard and plays hard will surely make such a person ecstatic.

50036.name: Guqin Music Scores
50036.desc: Music scores for Guqin that was found on a traveling merchant in Xu Heng District. If given to a mod who enjoys playing Guqin, they will surely cherish such a gift...

50039.name: Floral Patterned Sachet
50039.desc: A perforated perfume packet, wearable around the neck and made as an imitation of an antique. The original is part of some antique collector's collection in Xu Heng District. It may just be an imitation, but it still has great value as a collectible. A great gift for antique lovers.

50040.name: Comic Book: Commemorative Issue
50040.desc: A commemorative issue of a comic book series. Comic book collectors will surely love it!

50041.name: Mahjong Set
50041.desc: A set of mahjong tiles found at a handicrafts shop on East Banchuan Street. It would make a great gift for someone who likes to play this game.

50042.name: Oolong Qingshan
50042.desc: Native to Xu Heng's North Isle, these alpine tea leaves were prepared through a traditional semi-fermentation process. They'd probably make a nice gift for a tea connoisseur...

50043.name: Street Shōgi
50043.desc: Shogi is a popular game throughout Shimogyou District, and seasoned players will even customize their own boards to spice up the game.

50044.name: Wensi Tofu
50044.desc: Tender, mild, melt-in-your-mouth tofu made with carefully selected ingredients and exquisite knife work. Just one spoonful of the clear, delectable broth leaves an unforgettable flavor on the tongue.

50045.name: Gold Lacquer Folding Fan
50045.desc:
An example of traditional Sasanami craftsmanship, this tasteful gold lacquer folding fan features elegant patterns.
Gazing at the fan, you can almost see the ebbs and flows of Sasanami's high society over the course of history.

50046.name: Claw Machine Souvenir Coin
50046.desc: A limited edition Toy City Souvenir Coin. Only one is issued each year, and it is only given to the person who collects the most claw machine dolls. I wonder what that person's facial expression will look like when they're given this gift?

50047.name: Burr Puzzle
50047.desc: A burr puzzle made in Xu Heng, with equal weight given to modern technology and traditional workmanship. Light shines through the traditional materials, illuminating every nook. The perfect gift for a scientist.

50048.name: White Musk Fragrance
50048.desc: A non-flammable white musk fragrance with a refreshing and comforting scent. It'll make a good gift for someone who's really stressed out.

50049.name: Piece of Cake
50049.desc: A slice of white chocolate and sesame cake topped with pomegranate jam for a decadent texture. That person who really likes cutting cake into slices will probably ask you to taste it, right?

50050.name: Cantaloupe Macaroon
50050.desc: The fresh, fruity flavor of cantaloupe blended perfectly into a macaroon pastry. If you're a macaroon lover, you won't stop eating these until they run out!

50051.name: Vinyl Record
50051.desc: Listening to a vinyl record, it's just like you were there. This album features the music of the top Omorfies chamber ensemble, just the kind of music that would bring solace to a lighthouse keeper on a lonely, isolated island.

50052.name: Coconut Curry
50052.desc: Packed in a convenient and heat-retaining container, this curry has a robust aroma, rich flavor, and a lasting aftertaste. Even picky children won't be able to resist the veggies inside! This dish is the perfect way to cheer up a partner who's been busy with gang business!

51011.name: Chitterlings
51011.desc: Chitterlings. Full of flavor with a rich texture.

51023.name: Fresh Greens
51023.desc: Fresh greens imported from Xu Heng. These nutritious greens were grown by professionals in greenhouses.

51024.name: Chili Pepper
51024.desc: Chili pepper. Full of spice, brightly red.

51025.name: Tomato
51025.desc: Tomato. Juicy and sweet, with a tinge of sourness.

51030.name: Tofu
51030.desc: Bean-curd. Soft and exquisite, smooth and moist.

51031.name: Dumpling Wrappers
51031.desc: Wrappers for dumplings. Soft but chewy, gives a solid texture.

51032.name: Potato
51032.desc: Potato. Crispy on the outside when fried, soft when boiled.

52001.name: Interlock Crystals
52001.desc:
Crystals resulting from intersecting world lines, data streams from different worlds are contained within them.
—Countless worlds converge here.

52002.name: Guild EXP
52002.desc:
EXP obtained from completing guild missions that can be used to increase your guild level.
—May we join hands in the fight to amend the future.

53001.name: Imago Fragment
53001.desc:
Can be used to redeem Imago Gift rewards.
—It looks no different from a building block with its bronze appearance, but it seems to have been stripped from the Imago maze of a certain Mod.

53002.name: Absolute timestamp item for use in testing

53003.name: Selene's Music Score
53003.desc: A special score left behind by Senator Selene. The writing on it is so messy though, hardly can anyone read it.

53004.name: Limited Regular Scan Voucher
53004.desc:
A data card that allows access to Mimir's vibrant resonation. Used to scan for Modifiers in a given area within a certain period of time. Administrators are requested to pay close attention to the available time window.
—As resonation imprints require a large amount of computational power from the Mimir system, activation authority has to be strictly controlled.

53005.name: Limited Regular Scan Voucher
53005.desc:
A data card that allows access to Mimir's vibrant resonation. Used to scan for Modifiers in a given area within a certain period of time. Administrators are requested to pay close attention to the available time window.
—As resonation imprints require a large amount of computational power from the Mimir system, activation authority has to be strictly controlled.

53006.name: Dazzling Album
53006.desc:
A special crystal disc used to record Source Layer data, it's very fragile.
—Please transport with care.

53007.name: Variation Data Block
53007.desc: With the Society of Muses' help, Heimdall developed a crystal block that can quickly record elemental data on the battlefield.

53008.name: Vortex Powder
53008.desc: Data crystals from the Devouring Vortex. Turn them in to receive upgrade permissions for Matrix Modules.

53009.name: Limited Regular Scan Voucher
53009.desc:
A data card that allows access to Mimir's vibrant resonation. Used to scan for Modifiers in a given area within a certain period of time. Administrators are requested to pay close attention to the available time window.
—As resonation imprints require a large amount of computational power from the Mimir system, activation authority has to be strictly controlled.

53010.name: Mew Chips
53010.desc:
Card game chips which can be redeemed for rewards in Bastet's card game.
—Homemade gaming chips with cat silhouettes printed on them. They say that more and more people started playing after the change... But maybe that's not entirely down to the chips.

53011.name: Intel Module
53011.desc: The intel-gathering device that Jackal keeps on hand. Turn in Intel Modules at the Intel Terminal to redeem for supplies.

53012.name: Twilight Jade
53012.desc: Twilight fragments attached to the body of Nian. Legend has it that it holds the anger and sorrow of generations of those who have faught against their own destiny. Of high academic and aesthetic value.

53013.name: Data Tube
53013.desc: Collected data that can be traded with the Cryptics for items you need.

53014.name: Tian Lu Card
53014.desc:
A trade card provided by Tian Lu Traders to their long-time partners. Can be traded for supplies at the Co-op Shop.
—Nothing is better than old friends and new goods.

53015.name: Tian Lu VIP Card
53015.desc:
A trade card provided by Tian Lu Traders to their most trusted partners. Can be traded for supplies at the Partner Store. 
—Trust and kindness will earn you gold and diamonds.

53016.name: Purgatory Fragment
53016.desc:
A fragment etched with over ten thousand years' worth of hatred, the surface emanates a powerful aura of sorrow... 
Can be traded for supplies at the Valleyrand Trading Post.

53017.name: Tian Lu Voucher
53017.desc:
A voucher given to Mods by Tian Lu Traders. Use it to trade for supplies at Tian Lu Firm.
—Those with talent don't always work hard, yet those who work hard will always earn more.

53018.name: Limited Regular Scan Voucher
53018.desc:
A data card that allows access to Mimir's vibrant resonation. Used to scan for Modifiers in a given area within a certain period of time. Administrators are requested to pay close attention to the available time window.
—As resonation imprints require a large amount of computational power from the Mimir system, activation authority has to be strictly controlled.

53019.name: Omnisight Seal
53019.desc:
Said to be blessed by Xu Heng's mythological creature Omnisight, these mysterious relics are scattered across Gaea. Use it to stamp on the Candlelit Card.
—Jade in a box waits for a good price. Talented minds wait for a moment to shine.

53020.name: Kaixi Ingot
53020.desc:
A special piece of memorabilia issued by Tian Lu Traders and Aether Gazer together.
—Thank you for your company this past year, Admin!

53021.name: Cat Paw Coin
53021.desc: A redemption token with the imprint of a cat paw on it, personally authenticated by Lord Mimir.

53022.name: Butterfly on Plum Blossom
53022.desc:
A commemorative badge that has plum blossoms and butterflies on its design, it can be bought from the souvenir stores in Xu Heng's photon rail station.
—A young lady's thoughts, accompanied by golden butterflies, flutter onto the plum blossoms.

53023.name: Job File
53023.desc:
A stamped document serving as proof of a job completed.
—From the signature... it would appear that chief Gengchen has returned.

53024.name: Promissory Note
53024.desc: A token exclusive to Xu Heng gourmets, it can be exchanged for items used in Gourmet Outing event.

53025.name: Jigsaw Piece
53025.desc: Clearly, this is a mysterious puzzle piece. Collect all the pieces and complete the puzzle to obtain a mysterious clue.

53026.name: Positioner
53026.desc:
A positioning device that can correctly place puzzle pieces.
—"Lord Mimir has a hint for you, rookie."

53027.name: Midsummer Crystal
53027.desc: Stay a while in this never-ending summer.

53028.name: Songjade Pendant
53028.desc:
Can be used to redeem for rewards in the Lilt of the Green Hills event.
A handmade accessory carved from Songjade. Exquisite craftsmanship and elegant patterns. If you give it a gentle shake, you can hear a curious sound emitted from it like a dragon singing.

53029.name: Custom Souvenir Coin
53029.desc:
Shattered pieces of some glassy blue rose petals.
It represents a distant, unobtainable dream from another World Line.

53030.name: Special VIP Invite
53030.desc: A sophisticated invitation to a romantic banquet on the sea. There is an exclusive voucher customized by the yacht crew inside.

53031.name: Banquet Invite
53031.desc: A special invitation to a romantic banquet on the sea. There is an exclusive voucher customized by the yacht crew inside.

53032.name: Pinecone
53032.desc:
Can be used to exchange for rewards in Shimogyou Groceries.
A pinecone with a tiny hole chewed through it. But why was it left here?

53033.name: Candy Apple
53033.desc:
Exchange for a reward in the Shimogyou Market.
——Beautiful fireworks, don't you think?

53034.name: Positioner
53034.desc:
A positioning device that can correctly place puzzle pieces.
——"Lord Mimir has a hint for you, rookie."

53038.name: Chili Pepper
53038.desc: Chili pepper. Full of spice, brightly red.

53040.name: Flour
53040.desc: Wheat ground into a fine, snow-white powder.

53041.name: Red Bean
53041.desc: Red beans with a hint of sweetness and a delicate texture.

53042.name: Jujube
53042.desc: Sweet, juicy, and bright red jujubes.

53044.name: Sesame
53044.desc: Sweet and mellow black sesame seeds.

53045.name: Walnut
53045.desc: Crunchy and sweet walnuts with a lingering oiliness.

53046.name: Chestnut
53046.desc: Soft and sweet chestnuts with a dense texture.

53048.name: Meat Floss
53048.desc: Fluffy, dried meat with a sweet and savory flavor.

53049.name: Salted Egg Yolk
53049.desc: Rich and salty with a crumbly texture.

53050.name: Osmanthus
53050.desc: With a natural, sweet aroma refreshes the mind, it has a bitter taste that gives way to a lingering dulcet aftertaste.

53051.desc: Mooncake filling with game meat as the main ingredient.

53053.desc: Mooncake filling with red beans and jujubes as the main ingredients.

53054.name: Mixed Nuts Filling
53054.desc: Mooncake filling with peanuts, cashew nuts, and sesame seeds as the main ingredients.

53055.name: Meat Floss and Salted Egg Yolk
53055.desc: Mooncake filling with meat floss and salted egg yolk as the main ingredients.

53056.name: Floral Filling
53056.desc: Mooncake filling with osmanthus flowers as the main ingredient.

53057.desc: A meat mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53058.desc: A spicy mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53059.desc: A red bean and jujube mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53062.desc: A floral mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53063.desc: A meat mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53065.desc: A red bean and jujube mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53066.desc: A mixed nuts mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53067.desc: A meat floss and salted egg yolk mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53068.name: Floral - Square
53068.desc: A floral mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53069.desc: A meat mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53070.desc: A spicy mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53071.name: Red Bean and Jujube - Flower
53071.desc: A red bean and jujube mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53072.name: Mixed Nuts - Flower
53072.desc: A mixed nuts mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53073.name: Meat Floss and Salted Egg Yolk - Flower
53073.desc: A meat floss and salted egg yolk mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53074.name: Floral - Flower
53074.desc: A floral mooncake with just a slightly different exterior.

53075.name: Mystery - Classic
53075.desc: A mooncake of a flavor that is difficult to identify. It smells like socks that haven't been washed in months, and only its shape gives any indication that it's a mooncake... probably.

53076.name: Mystery - Square
53076.desc: A mooncake of a flavor that is difficult to identify. It smells like socks that haven't been washed in months, and only its shape gives any indication that it's a mooncake... probably.

53077.name: Mystery - Flower
53077.desc: A mooncake of a flavor that is difficult to identify. It smells like socks that haven't been washed in months, and only its shape gives any indication that it's a mooncake... probably.

53078.name: Golden Handguard
53078.desc:
Exchanged in the Shimogyou Folklore Shop for rewards.
A sword accessory once used mainly for protection, these days it also has some market value as a collector's item.

53079.name: Message
53079.desc:
Exchanged at the Intelligence Hub for rewards.
—As the panicked islanders exchange survival tips, the girl prepares for the sacrifice.

53080.name: Smelting Scrap
53080.desc:
Exchanged at Tournament Logistics for rewards.
—Unrealized potential retaining no trace of their former humanity. All that remains of their lives are broken blades strewn about the arena.

53081.name: Clue Pouch
53081.desc: Use in When Justice Shines to obtain a Clue Fragment.

53082.name: Nutrient Extract
53082.desc:
